Wowza. Lived up to the reputation. I had the Crawfish Boil Sausage footlong and my wife had the Shrimp Banh Banh. Definitely get the footlong as it's only a couple bucks more than the 6". But I digress...that boil sausage was ridiculous. The smoke off that thing was so prominent, and the quality of meat was through the roof. Tasted like a fresh meat locker smells. Spicy but only gets to tingling after half a sandwich. The shrimp one I didn't like as much but my wife loved it. Bread was a touch dry but you don't notice unless you're thinking about it. We also had the Mimi's Mac & Cheese. It's a spaghetti noodle dish with more melted cheese than I've ever seen. It was like a spaghetti bake. It was roll-yer-eyes back good. The star of the show. $1 Miller High Life pony bottles. Will definitely return. 4.5 stars/A-.

So, I went to Old Tyme Grocery right down the road. Since they were able to read a letter, I am now enjoying a beer and a Poboy.  Edit: Understand the owners response and appreciate it. However, the state issued letter makes my license valid with a 2024 expiration date. So, according to the letter it is a valid, current license with my picture on it. As the state laws require. I did not see in the response from the state saying the letter does not make my license valid. Regardless I have the renewed license now, so that's good. I'd go back here for tasty Poboys.  With all that said I agree to disagree and can appreciate them protecting their business.
